  "content": {
    "bodyModel": {
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_0",
          "href": null,
          "name": "305e",
          "text": "On the Felt Experience of Mental Framing",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "H3"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_1",
          "href": null,
          "name": "a9d7",
          "text": "Being outside the social context of others creates stress and pressure on your body.",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*m_JNN-9LMPtP5LioUttR1A.png",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_2",
          "href": null,
          "name": "0698",
          "text": "Why is it so stressful to go against the current of a culture? The answer has to do with mental constructs known as “frames” and the immense social pressures to conform when emotions run strong.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "9579",
          "text": "The concept of a mental frame has become more widely known in recent years — that human thought is structured within the body as emergent patterns with implicit logics, structured roles and relationships, and emotional sensibilities.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 29,
              "href": "http://www.cognitivepolicyworks.com/resource-center/frame-analysis-framing-tutorials/",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 4,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "0dc5",
          "text": "The frame for a glass of water has properties like containment and the ability to hold things, and graspability because it is something that fits in a human hand. This means we can think about and act upon a glass of water (filling the role of person-holding-the-glass) because there is a mental frame inside our brains that is wired into our neural circuitry as orchestrated patterns of gestures from every time we have interacted with a glass of water in the past.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 62,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 51,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 111,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 99,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "9ab9",
          "text": "I have worked with the tools of frame semantics for more than a decade now, analyzing language patterns to reveal their underlying conceptual structures that shape thought, feeling, and action on a wide variety of topics. This is the intellectual part of being a cognitive linguist.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 47,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 32,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "a7bf",
          "text": "What I want to talk about today is the felt experience of being in a social setting where others are “stuck inside a frame” that has become pathological. When a person experiences the jarring separation and immense social pressure to conform — because humans are such social creatures. We feel the judgments and discomforts of this social separation throughout our entire being.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "acf7",
          "text": "Said another way, your body will become emotionally stressed if you don’t conform to the accepted frame a community is acting out. If you want to understand what is going on in that situation — how the mental frames function like an echo chamber of shared perception keeping those inside from recognizing how their internal patterns conflict with patterns in the world — you will need to prepare yourself for the physical pressure of judgment and conformity by those around you.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 130,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 18,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 333,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 315,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 371,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 347,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "6253",
          "text": "I have been actively practicing this art of discernment in the US political process throughout the year. As waves of sentiment sweep across the social media landscape ( “Feel the Bern!”; “Fear Trump!!”; “Vote for Hillary or Trump will push the nuclear button!!!), I have watched the various ways that the media has been framing each situation. Earlier in the year, it was the combination of three factors:",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_9",
          "href": null,
          "name": "de5c",
          "text": "A near-total media blackout where corporate news refused to acknowledge the existence of Bernie Sanders campaign.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "OLI"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_10",
          "href": null,
          "name": "287b",
          "text": "A consistent mandate that all references to other candidates be juxtaposed with the candidacy of Hillary Clinton.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "OLI"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_11",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e3f2",
          "text": "Massive unwarranted exposure for Donald Trump as a media sensation.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "OLI"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_12",
          "href": null,
          "name": "77fd",
          "text": "This context placed all other candidates in inferior roles, culminating in a pronounced emphasis on the epic battle ascending between Clinton and Trump.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 115,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 104,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_13",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7d1f",
          "text": "Never mind that a consistent series of procedural issues kept revealing how corrupt the democratic process had become in the Democratic Party. Or that the Republican Party is built on an extreme disconnect from empirical reality. The party line (pun intended?) has been that there are only two legitimate political options and each is associated with an establishment institution in the form of one political party or the other.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 322,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 275,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_14",
          "href": null,
          "name": "9704",
          "text": "I wrote about this phenomenon as a system of political mind control last week. What I want to convey now is how essential it is for anyone working outside these establishment frames to recognize that their bodies will be stress-tested every time they push back against the echo chamber of perceptions around them.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 59,
              "href": "https://medium.com/@joe_brewer/the-illusion-of-power-is-a-kind-of-real-power-d0ba1dce8e9f#.t515pvou1",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 35,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 181,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 147,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_15",
          "href": null,
          "name": "18fe",
          "text": "Why is this important? Because there is a convergence of serious threats to humanity in the world — rising inequality, rampant political corruption, the cancerous logic of growth in our capitalist system, and all the social/ecological harms that flow from these things.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_16",
          "href": null,
          "name": "be2a",
          "text": "Now is the time when discernment is more important than ever. The ability to step outside of frames in the dominant culture is a vital move for all of us working to create systemic solutions to this planetary-scale crisis.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 61,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 222,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 62,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_17",
          "href": null,
          "name": "0f0a",
          "text": "This requires training. I have practiced martial arts, meditation, theater and dance throughout my adult life. I do this because it enables me to cultivate the bodily capacities to stand under pressure, feel into and be aware of my body states, and step out of the roles projected onto me by others in the theater of their minds.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_18",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b414",
          "text": "It is not simply an intellectual ability. This is an experiential, body-based practice. And it is one of the skill sets lacking in the world that must rapidly be cultivated en masse for us to navigate the endless string of crises yet to come. The lack of these skills is the real reason we are not seeing collective actions on the global crisis.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 229,
              "href": "https://medium.com/art-marketing/cultivating-empathy-for-the-next-crisis-8c7c9e909b6f#.h0gncmvf0",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 205,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 286,
              "href": "https://medium.com/@joe_brewer/why-dont-we-take-action-on-the-global-crisis-ff6bc3801d1a#.qu76xn1r5",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 275,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_19",
          "href": null,
          "name": "ea22",
          "text": "I hope this short essay, in some small way, can help shed light on the need for cultivating the human capacities for non-conformist critical thought. As I’ve said elsewhere, Now is THE Time to be rooted in reality and it is going to require active effort — a lot of hard emotional and physical work — to step outside the standard frames of dominant cultures worldwide and practice seeing what is really going on.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 213,
              "href": "https://medium.com/@joe_brewer/now-is-the-time-to-be-rooted-in-reality-6d148f62ca39#.fqd5a36f0",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 174,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 214,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 174,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1d4421f2be89_20",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7e46",
          "text": "Onward, fellow humans.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
